BASIC.Definition: (slang) someone or something as unoriginal, unexceptional, and mainstream

TOUGH.Definition: difficult to do or to deal with

ENGINEER.Definition: a person whose job is to design or build machines, engines, or electrical equipment, or things such as roads, railroads, or bridges, using scientific principles

AEROSPACE.Definition: producing or operating aircraft or spacecraft

SEMESTER.Definition: one of the periods into which a year is divided at a college or university, especially in the U.S. and Australia

DROPPED OUT.Definition: to not do something that you were going to do, or to stop doing something before you have completely finished

UNIQUE.Definition: being the only existing one of its type or, more generally, unusual, or special in some way

CURIOUS.Definition: interested in learning about people or things around you

DAMN.Definition: often used to express annoyance, disgust, or surprise
